<tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>11541</anchor> <rss>erct-001J.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>erct-001J</addr>  <route>erct-001J.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>20</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Sets</title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-001J.agda" type="external">erct-001J.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>A type <tex>A</tex> is called a <em><strong>set</strong></em> when for each <tex>x,y:A</tex> the identification type <tex>x=y</tex> is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link>.</p></mainmatter> <backmatter><contributions/> <context><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>11542</anchor> <rss>erct-003P.rss.xml</rss>  <addr>erct-003P</addr>  <route>erct-003P.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>20</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><link href="erct-001E.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001E" title="The truncation hierarchy">The truncation hierarchy</link> › basic definitions</title> <parent>erct-001E</parent> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>11543</anchor> <rss>erct-001H.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>erct-001H</addr>  <route>erct-001H.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>20</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Contractible type</title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-001H.agda" type="external">erct-001H.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>A type <tex>A</tex> is said to be <em><strong>contractible with centre <tex>a:A</tex></strong></em> when every <tex>x:A</tex> is equipped with an identification <tex>\chi _x \colon  a = x</tex>. We say that <tex>A</tex> is <em><strong>contractible</strong></em> when it comes equipped with some <tex>a:A</tex> such that <tex>A</tex> is contractible with centre <tex>a</tex>. We sometimes refer to a contractible type as a <em><strong>singleton</strong></em>.</p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>11544</anchor> <rss>erct-001I.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>erct-001I</addr>  <route>erct-001I.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>20</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Proposition</title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-001I.agda" type="external">erct-001I.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>A type <tex>A</tex> is said to be a <em><strong>proposition</strong></em> when every <tex>x:A</tex>, the type <tex>A</tex> is <link href="erct-001H.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001H" title="Contractible type">contractible with centre</link> <tex>x</tex>, i.e. all elements of <tex>A</tex> are identified.</p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>11545</anchor> <rss>erct-001J.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>erct-001J</addr>  <route>erct-001J.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>20</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Sets</title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-001J.agda" type="external">erct-001J.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>A type <tex>A</tex> is called a <em><strong>set</strong></em> when for each <tex>x,y:A</tex> the identification type <tex>x=y</tex> is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link>.</p></mainmatter> </tree><p>The notions of <link href="erct-001H.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001H" title="Contractible type">contractible</link> and <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">propositional</link> types generate an infinite hierarchy of <em>truncation levels</em> expressing the point after which higher identifications become trivial.</p><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>11546</anchor> <rss>erct-001F.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Convention</taxon> <addr>erct-001F</addr>  <route>erct-001F.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>20</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Indexing of truncation levels</title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-001F.agda" type="external">erct-001F.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>A <em><strong>truncation level</strong></em> is an integer <tex>n  \geq  -2</tex>.</p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>11547</anchor> <rss>erct-001G.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>erct-001G</addr>  <route>erct-001G.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>20</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><span style="white-space: nowrap"><tex>n</tex>-truncated</span> type</title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-001G.agda" type="external">erct-001G.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Given a <link href="erct-001F.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001F" title="Indexing of truncation levels">truncation level</link> <tex>n</tex>, we define what it means for a type to be <em><strong><span style="white-space: nowrap"><tex>n</tex>-truncated</span></strong></em> by induction:</p><ul><li>a type is <em><strong><span style="white-space: nowrap"><tex>-2</tex>-truncated</span></strong></em> when it is <link href="erct-001H.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001H" title="Contractible type">contractible</link>;</li>
  <li>a type is <em><strong><span style="white-space: nowrap"><tex>-1</tex>-truncated</span></strong></em> when it is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link>;</li>
  <li>for <tex>n  \geq  0</tex>, a type <tex>A</tex> is <em><strong><span style="white-space: nowrap"><tex>n</tex>-truncated</span></strong></em> when for every <tex>x,y:A</tex> the identification type <tex>x=y</tex> is <span style="white-space: nowrap"><tex>n-1</tex>-truncated</span>.</li></ul><p>So, in particular, a <tex>0</tex>-truncated type is precisely a <em>set</em>. We shall often refer to <span style="white-space: nowrap"><tex>n</tex>-truncated</span> types as <em><strong><span style="white-space: nowrap"><tex>n</tex>-types</span></strong></em>.</p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>11548</anchor> <rss>erct-001T.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>erct-001T</addr>  <route>erct-001T.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>20</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><span style="white-space: nowrap"><tex>n</tex>-truncated</span> map</title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-001T.agda" type="external">erct-001T.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>A function <tex>f \colon  A  \to  B</tex> is called <em><strong><span style="white-space: nowrap"><tex>n</tex>-truncated</span></strong></em> when all of its <link href="erct-001Q.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001Q" title="Fiber">fibers</link> are <link href="erct-001G.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001G" title="N-truncated type"><span style="white-space: nowrap"><tex>n</tex>-truncated</span> types</link>. By analogy, we shall also refer to maps as <em><strong>contractible</strong></em> when their fibers are; we shall refer to maps as <em><strong>propositional</strong></em> when their fibers are <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">propositions</link>.</p></mainmatter> </tree></mainmatter> </tree></context> <related><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>11549</anchor> <rss>erct-001I.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>erct-001I</addr>  <route>erct-001I.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>20</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Proposition</title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-001I.agda" type="external">erct-001I.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>A type <tex>A</tex> is said to be a <em><strong>proposition</strong></em> when every <tex>x:A</tex>, the type <tex>A</tex> is <link href="erct-001H.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001H" title="Contractible type">contractible with centre</link> <tex>x</tex>, i.e. all elements of <tex>A</tex> are identified.</p></mainmatter> </tree></related> <backlinks><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>11550</anchor> <rss>erct-001L.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Lemma</taxon> <addr>erct-001L</addr>  <route>erct-001L.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>20</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">Propositions</link> are <link href="erct-001J.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001J" title="Sets">sets</link></title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-001L.agda" type="external">erct-001L.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>If a type <tex>A</tex> is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link>, then it is a <link href="erct-001J.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001J" title="Sets">set</link>.</p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>11551</anchor> <rss>erct-001N.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Lemma</taxon> <addr>erct-001N</addr>  <route>erct-001N.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>20</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Being <link href="erct-001H.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001H" title="Contractible type">contractible</link> is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link></title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-001N.agda" type="external">erct-001N.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>It is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link> that a given type <tex>A</tex> is <link href="erct-001H.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001H" title="Contractible type">contractible</link>.</p>
 
   
   <tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="false" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>11552</anchor>  <taxon>Proof</taxon>    <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>20</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors>  <parent>erct-001N</parent> </frontmatter> <mainmatter>
  <p>Suppose we have two centres of contraction <tex>a,a':A</tex> with <tex>\chi _ \bullet \colon   \mathchoice { \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptscriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } } a = x</tex> and <tex>\chi '_ \bullet \colon \mathchoice { \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptscriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } } a'=x</tex> as witnesses of contraction. To identify <tex>\mathopen {} \left ( a, \chi _ \bullet \right ) \mathclose {}</tex> with <tex>\mathopen {} \left ( a', \chi '_ \bullet \right ) \mathclose {}</tex>, we employ the <link href="erct-0035.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0035" title="Covariant sum of an cocartesian family of path objects">covariant sum</link> of each of the <link href="erct-001C.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001C" title="Dependent product of path objects">pointwise path object</link> structures on <tex>\mathchoice { \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptscriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } } -=x</tex> over the <link href="erct-0013.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0013" title="The intrinsic path object">intrinsic path object</link> structure on <tex>A</tex>, constructing an identification <tex>p \colon  a = a'</tex> followed by a homotopy <tex>H  \colon   \mathopen {} \left ( \mathopen {} \left ( \chi _{a'} \right ) \mathclose {} _*^{ \mathchoice { \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptscriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } } -=x}  \chi _ \bullet \right ) \mathclose {}   \sim   \chi '_ \bullet</tex>. Fixing <tex>z \colon  A</tex>, we compute:</p>

  <tex display="block">      \begin {aligned}        \mathopen {} \left ( \mathopen {} \left ( \chi _{a'} \right ) \mathclose {} _*^{ \mathchoice { \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptscriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } } -=x}  \chi _ \bullet \right ) \mathclose {}  z       &amp;=        \mathopen {} \left ( \chi _{a'} \right ) \mathclose {} _*^{-=z}  \chi _z        \\        &amp;=        \chi _{a'} ^{-1}   \cdot   \chi _z        \\        &amp;=  \chi '_z      \end {aligned}   </tex>

  <p>The first and second steps follow from general computation lemmas for transport, and the last step follows from the fact that <tex>A</tex> is a <link href="erct-001J.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001J" title="Sets">set</link>, which we may deduce from <ref addr="erct-001K" href="erct-001K.xml" taxon="Lemma"/> and <ref addr="erct-001L" href="erct-001L.xml" taxon="Lemma"/>.</p>
</mainmatter> </tree>
 
</mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>11553</anchor> <rss>erct-000B.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>erct-000B</addr>  <route>erct-000B.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>3</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Precategory</title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-000B.agda" type="external">erct-000B.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>A <em><strong>precategory</strong></em> <tex>C</tex> is specified by the following data:</p><ol><li>a type <tex>\left \lvert C \right \rvert</tex> of <em>objects</em>, written <tex>c \in  C</tex>;</li>
  <li>for each <tex>x,y \in  C</tex> a <link href="erct-001J.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001J" title="Sets">set</link> <tex>C \mathopen {} \left ( x , y \right ) \mathclose {}</tex> of <em>arrows</em>, written <tex>f \colon  x \to  y</tex>;</li>
  <li>for each <tex>x \in  C</tex>, an <em>identity arrow</em> <tex>1_{ x } \colon  x \to  x</tex>;</li>
  <li>for each <tex>f \colon  x \to  y</tex> and <tex>g \colon  y \to  z</tex>, a <em>composite arrow</em> <tex>g \circ  f \colon  x  \to  z</tex>;</li>
  <li>such that composition is associative and unital with respect to identity arrows:
    <tex display="block">        \boldsymbol { \lambda }_{ f } \colon   1_{ y } \circ  f = f \quad         \boldsymbol { \rho }_{ f } \colon  f \circ   1_{ x }  = f  \quad         \boldsymbol { \alpha }_{ f , g , h } \colon   \mathopen {} \left ( h \circ  g \right ) \mathclose {} \circ  f = h \circ \mathopen {} \left ( g \circ  f \right ) \mathclose {}      </tex></li></ol></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>11554</anchor> <rss>erct-0001.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>erct-0001</addr>  <route>erct-0001.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>2</day></date><date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>2</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Displayed precategory</title>  </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>A <em><strong>displayed precategory</strong></em> <tex>C</tex> over a <link href="erct-000B.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000B" title="Precategory">precategory</link> <tex>B</tex>, written <tex>B \vdash  C</tex>, is specified by the following data:</p><ol><li>for each <tex>b \in  B</tex>, a type <tex>\left \lvert C \right \rvert b</tex> of <em>displayed objects</em> over <tex>b</tex> that we shall write <tex>b.c \in  C</tex>;</li>
  <li>for each <tex>b_0.c_0, b_1.c_1 \in  C</tex> and <tex>i \colon  b_0 \to  b_1</tex>, a <link href="erct-001J.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001J" title="Sets">set</link> <tex>C  _{ i } \mathopen {} \left ( b_0.c_0 , b_1.c_1 \right ) \mathclose {}</tex> of <em>displayed arrows</em> over <tex>i</tex>;</li>
  <li>for each <tex>b.c \in  C</tex> a displayed <em>identity arrow</em> <tex>1_{ b } . 1_{ c } \colon  b.c \to  b.c</tex>;</li>
  <li>for each <tex>i.f \colon  b_0.c_0 \to  b_1.c_1</tex> and <tex>j.g \colon  b_1.c_1 \to  b_2.c_2</tex>, a displayed <em>composite arrow</em> <tex>\mathopen {} \left ( j \circ  i \right ) \mathclose {} \circ \mathopen {} \left ( g \circ  f \right ) \mathclose {} \colon  b_0.c_0  \to  b_1.c_1</tex>;</li>
  <li>such that composition is associative and unital with respect to displayed identity arrows.</li></ol></mainmatter> </tree></backlinks> <references/></backmatter></tree>